The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on Monday congratulated theatre group Spandan, an IPTA faction, for getting an invitation to perform abroad. Spandan will perform at the Bonn Biennale, Germany, on May 19.

 hattacharjee, CPM state secretary Biman Bose and former chief minister Jyoti Basu greeted 15 members of Spandan at the party?s Alimuddin Street office. ?I am very proud and happy,? Bhattacharjee told Spandan writer-director Sangram Guha. ?Spandan is a brilliant theatre group of Calcutta,? added Basu. 

 Kumar Prasad Mukherjee, renowned musicologist who was also a vocalist and former director of Coal India, died of cancer on Sunday night. He was 79 and is survived by his wife.

 ukherjee was a disciple of Ustad Mushtaq Hussain Khan of the Gwalior/Sahaswan gharana and Ustad Latafat Hussain Khan of the Agra gharana, and was deeply influenced by the legendary Ustad Faiyaz Khan. Violinist V.G. Jog accompanied his recitals. 

 e had a passion for photography, cricket and adventure sports, having rafted down Devaprayag and Rishikesh and explored the Pindari Glacier and the Great Barrier Reef. 

 e was the son of Dhurjati Prasad Mukherjee, sociologist, litterateur and musicologist. His literary flair came to the fore in books such as Kudrat Rangi Birangi, Dishi Gaan Biliti Khela, Majlis in Bengali and the recent The Lost World of Hindustani Music.

 ukherjee was assigned by Ford Foundation and Sangeet Research Academy (SRA) to study the characteristics of gharanas. But the 1,000 cassettes that he had recorded have yet to see the light of day. They are locked up in SRA. 

 Two persons were critically injured when the motorcycle they were riding was hit by a private bus on route 79D on VIP Road late on Sunday. The injured were admitted to a nursing home.

 A Howrah-Sakherbazar minibus and a private bus, plying on route 208, collided at the crossing of Kiron Shankar Roy Road and Strand Road at 11.25 am on Monday. Police said Amar Naskar, conductor of the minibus, was admitted to SSKM Hospital with serious head injuries. One of the drivers has been held and both buses have been impounded.

 The parks and gardens wing of the civic body has decided to take up large-scale plantation of fruit trees in the monsoon. Mayoral council member Faiyaz Ahmed Khan said the saplings, around 5,000, will be planted mostly on the banks of drainage channels.

 Two persons committed suicide by hanging themselves in Howrah early on Sunday. Police said 30-year-old Lakshmi Kanta Kapat was found hanging at his Natun Pally home, under Sankrail police station. Suman Ghoshal, 30, was found hanging from a tree near his residence in Pratappur, under Jagachha police station.

 Calcutta High Court on Monday upheld the life imprisonment of Danyen Hossain and Abuzar Hossain, convicted for the murder of Congress leader Mohammed Jahangir in Kidderpore. Jahangir, alias Mughal, was killed on February 11, 2003. 

 Sahadeb Sapui, 28, was run over by a truck on Diamond Harbour Road in Bishnupur, on the southern fringes of the city, on Monday. morning. Police said Sapui was riding a motorcycle. The driver was arrested.

